\id 2SA - Plain English Version - 1 Samuel selections; Alice Springs 12 Dec 2018 (Blackman AuSIL)
\h 2 Samuel
\toc3 2 Samuel
\toc2 2 Samuel
\toc1 2 Samuel
\mt1 The Story about the big boss called David
\mt2 (From the book in the Holy Bible called \bk 2 Samuel\bk*)
\imt1 About this story
\ip These stories are about things that happened about 3,000 years ago, in the country called Israel.
\ip Somebody wrote these stories in a big book called \em Samuel\em* with lots of other stories, but it was too big, so they split it into 2 books, called \em 1 Samuel\em*, and \em 2 Samuel\em*. They were in God’s book, that the Jewish people had before Jesus came to this earth. They are now in the 1st part of the Holy Bible, called the \em Old Testament\em*.
\ip We have not yet translated all of the stories from 2 Samuel.
\ip The stories in this book are mostly about God’s man called David. In 1 Samuel we can read that God picked David to be the big boss of his people, but David did not become the big boss straight away. Saul was the first big boss. After he died, David became the big boss, but it was not always easy for him. He often had problems.
\ip These stories are important, and we can learn a lot from them. They help us know what God is like and what he planned for his people. They show us that God is always with his people, and that he helps them when they have problems.
\cl Chapter
\c 1
\s1 David heard the bad news about Saul
\p 
