\p \w At|strong="H5921"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* same \w time|strong="H5921"\w*, \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w Israel|strong="H3478"\w* mob \w ran|strong="H5127"\w* \w away|strong="H3947"\w* \w and|strong="H3478"\w* \w went|strong="H3478"\w* \w back|strong="H3947"\w* \w to|strong="H3478"\w* \w their|strong="H3605"\w* homes.
\b
\iex (We have not yet translated 18:18-31a. It tells how a messenger ran back to tell David the news.)
\b
\p 
\v 31 \w The|strong="H3605"\w* \w messenger|strong="H1319"\w* said, “Boss. \w Good|strong="H1319"\w* \w news|strong="H1319"\w*. \w God|strong="H3068"\w* \w still|strong="H3588"\w* wants \w you|strong="H3588"\w* \w to|strong="H3068"\w* \w be|strong="H3027"\w* \w our|strong="H3068"\w* big boss. \w Your|strong="H3068"\w* \w enemies|strong="H6965"\w* \w are|strong="H3117"\w* \w nothing|strong="H3605"\w* \w now|strong="H3117"\w*. \w He|strong="H3588"\w* punished \w them|strong="H5921"\w* properly.”
\p 
\v 32 David asked, “\w What|strong="H7451"\w* \w about|strong="H1961"\w* \w my|strong="H3605"\w* son Absalom? \w Is|strong="H3605"\w* \w he|strong="H3605"\w* \w all|strong="H3605"\w* right?”
\p \w The|strong="H3605"\w* messenger answered, “\w Those|strong="H3605"\w* \w trouble|strong="H7451"\w* makers, \w your|strong="H3605"\w* \w enemies|strong="H6965"\w*, \w I|strong="H5921"\w* hope \w they|strong="H5921"\w* \w all|strong="H3605"\w* finish \w up|strong="H6965"\w*, \w just|strong="H3605"\w* \w like|strong="H1961"\w* \w that|strong="H3605"\w* \w young|strong="H5288"\w* \w man|strong="H5288"\w* finished \w up|strong="H6965"\w*.”
\p 
\v 33 David got very upset. He went inside and cried. As he went in, he called out, “Absalom. My son Absalom. I want to be dead instead of you. You were my son.”
\b
\iex (We have not yet translated 19:1—21:14.)
\c 21
\s1 David’s mob fought with the Philistia mob again
\p 
\v 15 Some \w time|strong="H1961"\w* \w later|strong="H1961"\w*, \w the|strong="H1961"\w* \w Israel|strong="H3478"\w* mob \w went|strong="H3381"\w* \w to|strong="H3381"\w* \w fight|strong="H3898"\w* \w with|strong="H5973"\w* \w the|strong="H1961"\w* Philistia mob \w again|strong="H5750"\w*. \w David|strong="H1732"\w* \w also|strong="H1732"\w* \w went|strong="H3381"\w* \w with|strong="H5973"\w* \w his|strong="H1732"\w* \w soldiers|strong="H5650"\w*, \w to|strong="H3381"\w* \w fight|strong="H3898"\w* \w along|strong="H5973"\w* \w with|strong="H5973"\w* \w them|strong="H3381"\w*. \w But|strong="H1961"\w* \w soon|strong="H5750"\w*, \w he|strong="H1732"\w* got very \w tired|strong="H5774"\w*.
\v 16 \w Then|strong="H1732"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* really big Philistia man \w came|strong="H7969"\w* close \w to|strong="H1732"\w* \w David|strong="H1732"\w*. \w His|strong="H1732"\w* name \w was|strong="H1732"\w* Ishbibenob. \w He|strong="H1931"\w* belonged \w to|strong="H1732"\w* Rafa’s family. Everybody \w in|strong="H1732"\w* \w that|strong="H1931"\w* family \w was|strong="H1732"\w* really big \w and|strong="H3967"\w* strong. \w His|strong="H1732"\w* \w spear|strong="H7013"\w* \w had|strong="H1732"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* sharp point. \w It|strong="H1931"\w* \w was|strong="H1732"\w* heavy, 3½ kilograms, \w and|strong="H3967"\w* \w he|strong="H1931"\w* \w had|strong="H1732"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w new|strong="H2319"\w* long knife. \w He|strong="H1931"\w* reckoned \w he|strong="H1931"\w* \w was|strong="H1732"\w* going \w to|strong="H1732"\w* \w kill|strong="H5221"\w* \w David|strong="H1732"\w* dead.
\v 17 \w But|strong="H3808"\w* \w one|strong="H3808"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w David|strong="H1732"\w*’s boss \w soldiers|strong="H4421"\w* \w came|strong="H3318"\w* \w to|strong="H3318"\w* save \w him|strong="H5221"\w* \w from|strong="H3318"\w* \w that|strong="H3478"\w* big \w man|strong="H1121"\w*. \w He|strong="H1732"\w* \w attacked|strong="H5221"\w* \w the|strong="H5221"\w* big \w man|strong="H1121"\w* \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w killed|strong="H5221"\w* \w him|strong="H5221"\w* \w dead|strong="H4191"\w*. \w That|strong="H3478"\w* brave \w man|strong="H1121"\w* \w was|strong="H1732"\w* Abishai, \w the|strong="H5221"\w* \w son|strong="H1121"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w David|strong="H1732"\w*’s sister called \w Zeruiah|strong="H6870"\w*.\x * \xo 21:17 \xt 1 Kings 11:36; Psalm 132:17\x*
\p \w After|strong="H3318"\w* \w that|strong="H3478"\w*, \w David|strong="H1732"\w*’s \w men|strong="H1121"\w* \w made|strong="H7650"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w promise|strong="H7650"\w* \w to|strong="H3318"\w* \w him|strong="H5221"\w*. \w They|strong="H3808"\w* \w said|strong="H3318"\w*, “\w We|strong="H4191"\w* \w will|strong="H3478"\w* \w never|strong="H3808"\w* \w let|strong="H3808"\w* \w you|strong="H3808"\w* \w come|strong="H3318"\w* \w with|strong="H3318"\w* \w us|strong="H3478"\w* \w again|strong="H5750"\w* \w to|strong="H3318"\w* \w fight|strong="H4421"\w*. \w They|strong="H3808"\w* \w might|strong="H1121"\w* \w kill|strong="H4191"\w* \w you|strong="H3808"\w* \w dead|strong="H4191"\w*. \w You|strong="H3808"\w* \w are|strong="H1121"\w* \w like|strong="H3318"\w* \w the|strong="H5221"\w* \w lamp|strong="H5216"\w* \w in|strong="H3478"\w* \w God|strong="H3808"\w*’s ceremony house. \w Nobody|strong="H3808"\w* \w puts|strong="H4191"\w* \w out|strong="H3318"\w* \w its|strong="H5221"\w* fire. \w You|strong="H3808"\w* see, \w your|strong="H3808"\w* \w life|strong="H4191"\w* \w is|strong="H3478"\w* \w like|strong="H3318"\w* \w that|strong="H3478"\w*. \w We|strong="H4191"\w* don’t \w want|strong="H3808"\w* anybody \w to|strong="H3318"\w* \w kill|strong="H4191"\w* \w you|strong="H3808"\w* \w and|strong="H1121"\w* finish \w up|strong="H3318"\w* \w Israel|strong="H3478"\w*’s \w lamp|strong="H5216"\w*.”
\b
\iex (We have not yet translated 21:18—24:25. It is about some of the other things that David did before he died. The last bit of this story is from another book called the \em 1st book of the Big Bosses\em*. We call that book \em 1 Kings\em*, and these verses are from 1 Kings 2:10-12.)
\b
\p \add David died when he was an old man. They buried him in the city called Jerusalem, in that part of the city they call \em the city of David.\em* David was the big boss of Israel for 40 years. First he was the boss in the town called Hebron for 7 years, then he was the boss in Jerusalem for 33 years. Then David’s son Solomon became the big boss. He took over from his father and controlled the whole country. \add* 
